.TH GIMPCPT 1 "Jan 2004" Version @VERSION@ 
.SH NAME
.I gimpcpt
- convert 
.I Gimp
gradient files to 
.I GMT
palette files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gimpcpt
[
.BI \-b\  col
] 
[
.BI \-f\  col
] 
[
.B \-h
] 
[
.BI \-n\  col
]  
[
.BI \-o\  file
] 
[
.BI \-r\  range
] 
[
.BI \-s\  samples
] 
[
.BI \-t\  col
]  
[
.B \-v
] 
[
.B \-V
] 
[
.I file
]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The 
.I gimpcpt
utility converts gradient files from the
.IR Gimp , 
the GNU Image Manipulation Program, to the 
colour palette (.cpt) files used by 
.IR GMT , 
the generic mapping toolset. 

The generated palettes are piecewise linear ("continuous"
palettes in the GMT parlance) so  
.I makecpt 
should be
used convert them if a  piecewise constant ("discreet")
palette is required.

The program will read from stdin if a gradient is not
specified as the final argument, and write to stdout
if the 
.B \-o 
option is not specified. 
 
.SH OPTIONS
.l 
.I gimpcpt
accepts the following options:
.TP 8
.BI \-b\  colour
Set the palette background to 
.I colour.
.TP 8
.BI \-f\  colour
Set the palette foreground to 
.I colour.
.TP 8
.B  \-h
Display a list of all command line options.
.TP 8
.BI \-n\  colour
Set the palette NaN to 
.I colour.
.TP 8
.BI \-o\  file
Write the palette to 
.IR file , 
rather than stdout.
.TP 8
.BI \-r\  min/max
Set the palette range from
.I min
to 
.IR max .
.TP 8
.BI \-s\  samples
Specify the maximum number of samples. Gimp gradients allow for 
complex curves in a number of colour-space co-ordinate systems.
In order that these can be converted into GMT's simple RGB linear
splines we must sample these complex curves quite densely. The 
.I samples
parameter specifies (roughly) the maximum number of samples. In
the case that the Gimp gradient 
.I is
an RGB linear spline gradient the option has no effect, since
we can then convert the segments directly.
.TP 8
.BI \-t\  colour
Specify the colour to replace transparency. Gimp colours have
a level of transparency, but GMT palettes do not.
.TP 8
.B \-v
Verbose operation.
.TP 8
.B \-V
Output version info.

.SH FILES

The Gimp's data files are stored in subdirectories of  
${prefix}/share/gimp/${ver}/, 
where ${prefix} is set on install, but is typically /usr/local,
and ${ver} is the version number (1.2 at the time of writing).
.I gimpcpt
will search for files in the directories

The current directory

The directories specified in GIMP_GRADIENTS

.BR $HOME /.gimp-${ver}/gradients

/usr/share/gimp/${ver}/gradients

/usr/local/share/gimp/${ver}/gradients

where ${ver} ranges over feasible version numbers. 

.SH ENVIRONMENT

If the GIMP_GRADIENTS variable is defined then each
colon separated directory in the variable will be 
searched for gradient files.

